@Phat It's not necessarily the case that Hindi speakers don't care about pronunciation. Some languages are just harder or easier to pronounce for people from some other languages. 

For example, I'm Bengali and while I've been writing in English for many, many years, I've never really put any effort into sounding like a native speaker. Or more accurately, I don't have the fabled American accent that everyone wants to hear. And yet, every single native speaker that I've talked to in my life effortlessly understood me. This is simply because Bengalis don't have that strong of an accent (in English).

That said, I personally consider it disrespectful to ask people to abandon their accents when what they're saying is easily understood. Accents can vary region to region, person to person, even amongst native speakers themselves. So my suggestion for you is, if you ever find yourself pissed off at someone's accent even though you understand them clearly, stop and contemplate if it's the accent that's annoying to you or the simple fact that different people exist. I'm sure you'll learn your lesson at some point if you think hard enough.
